# BROWSER-restack.md - Substack Restack Patterns

## SS 10. Restack with a Note

🚨 **Radix UI dropdown:** Substack uses Radix UI for the Restack menu. MUST use `PointerEvent` sequence (`pointerdown` → `pointerup` → `click`).

🚨 **Finding the restack button:** The button has no aria-label. Find it as the 3rd button in the article's action bar (after Like and Comments). Use the LAST Like button group on the page — pages with embedded video/podcast have two action bars.

### Step 1 — Click Restack button and select "Restack with a note"

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); var likeBtns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')).filter(function(b) { return (b.getAttribute('aria-label') || '').startsWith('Like ('); }); if (likeBtns.length === 0) return { error: 'no like buttons found' }; var articleLike = likeBtns[likeBtns.length - 1]; var container = articleLike.parentElement.parentElement; var allBtns = Array.from(container.querySelectorAll('button')); var restackBtn = allBtns[2]; if (!restackBtn) return { error: 'no restack button at idx 2' }; var rect = restackBtn.getBoundingClientRect(); var cx = rect.x + rect.width / 2, cy = rect.y + rect.height / 2; restackBtn.dispatchEvent(new PointerEvent('pointerdown', { bubbles: true, clientX: cx, clientY: cy })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 50)); restackBtn.dispatchEvent(new PointerEvent('pointerup', { bubbles: true, clientX: cx, clientY: cy })); restackBtn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, clientX: cx, clientY: cy })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); var menuItems = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[role=\"menuitem\"]')); var quoteItem = menuItems.find(function(m) { return m.innerText.trim() === 'Restack with a note'; }); if (!quoteItem) return { error: 'menu not opened', items: menuItems.map(function(m) { return m.innerText.trim(); }) }; quoteItem.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); var editor = document.querySelector('div[contenteditable=\"true\"]'); return { opened: !!editor }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

### Step 2 — Type quote note and post

Use **BROWSER-note.md SS 9 Step 2** (identical Notes composer — contenteditable + "Post" button).

### When to Restack

Restack content aligned with your pillars with genuine {{role}} perspective. Skip off-topic, low-quality, self-restacks. Quote note: 1-3 sentences adding real value, not just "great post".
